Welcome to the '''PostGIS Raster''' project home page!

'''PostGIS Raster''' is an ongoing project aiming at developing '''raster support in PostGIS'''. It is a new project very different from the previous PGRaster project and also very different from [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GeoRaster Oracle Spatial GeoRaster].

The goal of '''PostGIS Raster''' is to implement the RASTER type '''as much as possible like the GEOMETRY type''' is implemented in PostGIS and to offer '''a single set of overlay SQL functions''' (like ST_Intersects) operating '''seamlessly''' on vector and raster coverages.

PostGIS Raster is now part of PostGIS starting with version 2.0 (spring 2012)!

== PostGIS Raster Google Summer of Code 2012 Ideas ==

This year again every projects submitted by OSGeo to the Google Summer of Code will be financed by Google. This means 5000 USD$ for a programming student summer job! See [http://trac.osgeo.org/postgis/wiki/WKTRasterGSoC our project list] or propose your own one! Every details [http://wiki.osgeo.org/wiki/Google_Summer_of_Code_2011_Ideas here] and [http://www.google-melange.com/document/show/gsoc_program/google/gsoc2011/faqs here]. Deadline to apply: April 8.

== Installation ==

 * '''Linux -''' Different repositories exist for binary versions of PostGIS. If no repository is available for your Linux flavor, you will have to [wiki:DevWikiMain compile PostGIS yourself].

 * '''Windows Binaries - ''' If you are running PostGIS on Windows, you can find fairly recent binaries of PostGIS 2.0 (including raster support) in the [http://postgis.net/windows_downloads Windows Experimental Builds section]. These are for PostgreSQL 8.4, 9.0, and upcoming 9.1. Note that development on the standalone wktraster project deployable on PostGIS 1.3-1.5 has stopped and all future versions and bug fixes of raster support will be packaged in the PostGIS 2.0 builds.  The last set of binaries for the wktraster stand-alone are also available on Windows experimental page for PostgreSQL 8.3,8.4,9.0 running for PostGIS 1.4-1.5.

 * '''Mac OSX Binaries - ''' If you are running PostGIS on Mac OSX leopard or Snow Leopard, you can find fairly recent binaries of PostGIS at [http://www.kyngchaos.com/software/postgres KyngChaos PostgreSQL GIS].

 * '''GDAL PostGIS Raster Driver - ''' A [http://trac.osgeo.org/gdal/wiki/frmts_wtkraster.html GDAL PostGIS raster driver] was developed following a [http://socghop.appspot.com/ Google Summer of Code 2009] grant obtained by [http://libregis.org/ Jorge Arevalo].

